HEADWORD: Capoch
<hw>Ca*poch"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Capoches</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[Cf. Sp.
<ets>capucho</ets>, It. <ets>cappucio</ets>, F. <ets>Capuce</ets>,
<ets>capuchon</ets>, LL. <ets>caputium</ets>, fr. <ets>capa</ets> cloak.
See <ets>Cap</ets>.]</ety> <def>A hood; especially, the hood attached to
the gown of a monk.</def>⟦br⟧
